Title : Eremaean province
Text : {{Use Australian English|date=January 2016}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}
The '''Eremaean province''' is a [[phytochorion|botanical region]] in [[Western Australia]], characterised by a desert climate. It is sometimes referred to as the ''dry and arid inland''<ref>{{Citation | author1=Gunawardene, Nihara | title=Arid zone ant communities of Western Australia | publication-date=2003 | publisher=Curtin University of Technology, Department of Environmental Biology | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/3769311 | accessdate=10 January 2016 }}</ref> or ''interior'' region of Western Australia<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article211877449 |title=The Interior of Western Australia. |newspaper=[[The Northam Advertiser |The Northam Advertiser (WA : 1895 - 1918; 1948 - 1954)]] |location=WA |date=16 July 1898 |accessdate=10 January 2016 |page=2 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=Warburton, Peter Egerton | author2=Bates, Henry Walter, 1825-1892 | author3=Eden, Charles H. (Charles Henry), 1839-1900 | title=Journey across the western interior of Australia | publication-date=1981 | publisher=Hesperian Press | edition=Facsimile | isbn=978-0-85905-031-9 }}</ref>

It is the central and largest of three botanical provinces defined for the state, the others being the Northern province and the [[Southwest Australia|Southwest province]].<ref name=florabase>{{cite web|title=A visual guide to the Interim Biogeographic Regionalisation for Australia (IBRA) in WA|work=FloraBase: The Western Australian Flora|publisher=Western Australian Herbarium|url= https://florabase.dpaw.wa.gov.au/help/ibra/|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref><ref>not specifically named in the 1928 discussion, however the other provinces are clearly identified {{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article32097395 |title=NATURAL REGIONS. |newspaper=[[Perth_Gazette|The West Australian (Perth, WA : 1879 - 1954)]] |location=Perth, WA |date=14 March 1928 |accessdate=10 January 2016 |page=14 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>

It contains 7 ecoregions that are recognised  in the [[Interim Biogeographic Regionalisation for Australia]] (IBRA):<ref name=florabase/>

*[[Carnarvon (biogeographic region)|Carnarvon]] (CAR)
*[[Central Ranges]] (CR)
*[[Coolgardie (biogeographic region)|Coolgardie]] (COO)
*[[Gascoyne]] (GAS)
*[[Gibson Desert]] (GD)
*[[Great Sandy Desert]] (GSD)
*[[Great Victoria Desert]] (GVD)
*[[Hampton (biogeographic region)|Hampton]] (HAM)
*[[Little Sandy Desert]] (LSD)
*[[Murchison (Western Australia)|Murchison]] (MUR)
*[[Nullarbor]] (NUL)
*[[Pilbara (biographic region)]] (PIL)
*[[Tanami (IBRA region)|Tanami]] (TAN)  
*[[Yalgoo (biogeographic region)|Yalgoo]] (YAL)

